    "body": "> If admins aren't kicked via this process, my initial instinct was to suggest that we keep the users in the All members tab and just give them another treatment / label. They technically are still members from an Admin perspective given they will automatically rejoin as soon as the new owner node comes online\r\n\r\nI think this makes sense!\r\n\r\nThe only caveat I would say, and correct me if I'm wrong @mprakhov , when a token master or an admin gets auto-accepted back  in the community, they will **not** have access to the same list of waiting users, so for them, it would look like the community is \"empty\".\r\nOnly the new owner will have the list as far as I know. \r\n\r\nIt's not a big deal IMO, we can still go for your idea as it looks better and doesn't need a new tab secction.",
